Police tape at crime scene [Courtesy]  A senior Wildlife Research and Training Institute official in Naivasha was yesterday found dead in his house.  The man, who had a wound on his head, had been seen the previous evening in a bar in Kayole estate in the town. “A postmortem will determine the cause of death. Our officers have opened an inquest file as part of investigations,” said Naivasha OCPD Samuel Waweru.  Meanwhile, one person died and six injured when a matatu hit a stalled lorry on the Nairobi-Nakuru highway.     By Jael Mboga | 4 hours ago By Antony Gitonga | 6 hours ago By Nikko Tanui | 7 hours ago By Irissheel Shanzu | 7 hours ago